originalText.text: small well-run neighborhood pharmacy for Lincoln Square, Hell’s Kitchen, etc. areas. headed here for a vaccination—they do a bunch of them…go to their site or call them for which ones. sadly, no Super Soldier serum is served here but getting my shot was supereasy and the process is straightforward. i was in and out in less than 15 minutes. the interior is clean and packed with a variety of over-the-counter items. the staff is friendly and organized—observed them helping other customers in a friendly manner. would definitely come back here if i had any other vaccine needs and they do notarization too by appointment, i believe.

originalText.text: I love having Danny's so close to my home. I've used their notary services many times and bought stamps and some items from them. I feel so lucky that they provide notary services! They are so friendly and always ready to help whenever I'm there. They are well stocked and their items are reasonably priced. I'm determined to support them to keep them in business! We need more local businesses like this.

originalText.text: Danny’s Pharmacy proudly and diligently serves the local community with compassion and expertise. The staff knows most customers by name and go the extra mile to help a diverse spectrum of neighborhood locals fill prescriptions, get clear and sound advice about medications, and obtain seasonal vaccines. Despite the pharmacy’s modest size and occasional (short) lines, staff are friendly and hardworking. There’s never an unending line of grim customers unsure whether their prescriptions are even ready! In fact, I’ve never seen an unsatisfied, much less irate, customer - something that’s  a norm at CVS and Walgreens. Danny and his team of pharmacists and staff make every effort to be helpful and compassionate, especially where it concerns filling vital prescriptions. We’re lucky to have Danny’s in the neighborhood!

originalText.text: Great asset to our community! Kind workers and excellent service, going above and beyond. My son was sick with pneumonia. I went to 5 different big pharmacies (cvs and Duane reade) with getting the medicines because out of stock. Danny’s had everything! Thank you, will be back!

originalText.text: I went to Urgent Care and they were no help. I should have gone straight to ask Danny. I know now! He knew immediately what would help and 24 hours later the swelling around my eyes (alergies) was down and the reddness much reduced. What a relief and I'm grateful!
